  behavior test, fix Gem.path test. 

2008-06-24  Ryan Davis <ryand-ruby@zenspider.com>

  * lib/rubygems/remote_fetcher.rb, test/test_gem_remote_fetcher.rb: Cleaned up
  tests a bit, since we use the stubs in such a similar way now. Removed
  test_zip and test_no_zip since they weren't actually testing anything.
  util_stub_connection_for now takes a straight hash. Conn class now takes a
  straight payload, since it was never used more than once. fetch_path now
  takes an optional head argument. Returns headers if true. fetch_size is now a
  beautiful 1 line long. open_uri_or_path also takes an optional head argument.
   

2008-06-24  Phil Hagelberg <phil@hagelb.org>

  * ChangeLog: added ChangeLog entries for ~/.gem fallback features.  

  * lib/rubygems.rb, lib/rubygems/installer.rb, test/gemutilities.rb: use
  MockGemUi in *all* tests, not just the ones that specify it.  

  * lib/rubygems/remote_fetcher.rb, test/test_gem_remote_fetcher.rb: Remote
  Fetcher should fall back to cache in ~ if regular cache isn't writable.  

  * test/test_gem.rb: fix path test  

  * test/gemutilities.rb, test/test_gem.rb: Don't need to munge nil if we
  use_ui in tests. Still, should use_ui automatically.  

  * lib/rubygems/defaults.rb: Add ~/.gem to default load path so people can
  actually use this stuff.  

  * lib/rubygems/installer.rb, test/test_gem_installer.rb: Check writability of
  bindir, create bindir in the right tests, use "say" properly.  Also wrap
  chmodding tests in "if not win_platform?"  

  * test/test_gem_remote_fetcher.rb: failing test case for downloading when
  cache dir and gem home are read only  

  * lib/rubygems/install_update_options.rb, lib/rubygems/installer.rb,
  test/gemutilities.rb, test/test_gem_install_update_options.rb,
  test/test_gem_installer.rb: Added command-line switch to force/deny
  user-level installations.  By default it falls back to user installation only
  if it can't write to gem home. You can force it to use ~/.gem with
  --user-install  Also added stdout/stderr redirecting to test setup/teardown. 

  * lib/rubygems/installer.rb, test/test_gem_installer.rb: fall back on ~/.gem
  if GEM_HOME is not writable  

  * test/test_gem_installer.rb: failing test for local gem installation  

