  versions has different numbers of subversions.  

2005-03-11  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb: Create the "gem dependency" command.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/version.rb: Unnested Requirement from Version class. 

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: Better uninstall confirmation prompt.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Switched to find_name.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/lib/rubygems/source_index.rb: update ChangeLog
   

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/source_index.rb: Added a find_name to SourceIndex to
  cover the common case of wanting an exact match on the short name. Renamed
  parameter to gem_pattern to emphasize the use of regular expressions in
  search.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Added comment to activate to clarify the return
  value. Refactored the activate command.  Errors are built out of line now.
  Autorequire is more faithfully tested.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Checking for dependencies should
  not user auto_require.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: Changed to call
  require_gem_with_options with auto_require => false.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb: Added ignore-dependencies option to
  command (but have not yet wired it in to the logic).  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Added require_gem_with_options to allow the
  passing of things like auto_require flags.  

