2004-12-04  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/source_index.rb: new file  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/test/yaml_data.rb: Renamed cache.rb to
  source_index.rb.  

  * rubygems/test/test_cache.rb: Broke up extremely long assert comment.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb: Rename class Cache to class SourceIndex and
  updated the rdocs. Cache is now an alias for SourceIndex.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_cached_fetcher.rb, rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb:
  renamed source_index on the remote installer to source_index_hash  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_cached_fetcher.rb, rubygems/test/test_remote_fetcher.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: renamed source_info to source_index  

  * rubygems/.cvsignore, rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: renamed flush to finish in
  MockFetcher  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added a finish call to
  RemoteSourceFetcher.  Currently it does nothing, but leave the class
  compatible with the cached fetcher. Added a finish method to CachedFetcher. 
  Called to initiate cache flushing. Changed to call finish rather than flush. 

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Improved default response when all the other
  options have been tried.  

2004-12-03  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/doc/rdoc_templates/jamis.rb: added Jamis Buck's rdoc template  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Updated some rdoc comments.  

  * rubygems/Releases: Reformatted to be in RDoc format.  

  * rubygems/Rakefile: Added rdoc and publish_rdoc targets to the Rakefile.  

  * rubygems/README: Reformatted in RDoc format.  

  * rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: oops, forgot to put flush on my
  MockFetcher object.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: change log updates  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added update and flush to the
  caching fetcher so that it can update its local cache files. Switched to
  using a cached fetcher in the remote installer.  All the caching logic was
  removed from the installer. write_gem_to_file now will create the path if
  needed.  

  * rubygems/test/test_local_cache.rb: Fixed write_cache test to use new arg
  list.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: made the cached data lazy load.
  write cache will now write only the current data in the memory cache. Missing
  cache files now handled. CachedFetcher now works cooperates with the local
  cache manager.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog comments.  

  * rubygems/test/gemutilities.rb, rubygems/test/test_local_cache.rb: added
  local cache manager object  

  * rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: Clear gem paths before running
  tests.  

  * rubygems/test/test_gempaths.rb: Added tests for the user home directory.  

  * rubygems/test/test_cached_fetcher.rb: Added gem utilities to test to aid in
  managing some test data.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added a local source info cache
  manager to implement the cache reading and writing policies.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Added a user home directory to the Gem module. 
  We use this to determine where to put the user writable cache file. use_paths
  now calls clear_paths  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: changelog updates.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Removed debugging prints
  accidently left in the code.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/package.rb: Versions of zlib earlier than 1.2.1 seem
  to have a problem. (Observed when installing RuWiki on windows).  Workaround:
  Read the zipped stream into a string and then creating a string IO object
  from the result seems to work around this problem.  

