2004-11-27  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Switched from open-uri with
  early abort to an HTTP.head call to get the size of the yaml file on the
  server.  

  * rubygems/Rakefile: Added task to find all the ruby files.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: more remote_installer changes  

  * rubygems/test/test_specification.rb: Added test to check some basic default
  values on a gem.  

  * rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: Made a "real" fake cache. Improved
  source_info test.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: Minor formatting.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: work on remote installer  

  * rubygems/test/test_package.rb: Made the unit test ignore the setgid bit. 
  The setgid bit does not work on my laptop for some reason.  This may be a
  problem with my laptop rather than with this code.  Should investigate
  further.  

  * rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: Added MockFetcher to make testing
  the remote installer easier. Currently there are two remote installer test
  classes.  Eventually TestRemoteInstaller will succeed RemoteInstallerTest,
  which is very incomplete.  

  * rubygems/test/functional.rb: Changed calls to match renaming of
  get_cache_sources to sources.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added a Fetcher object to the
  remote installer to handle all the details of getting the remote information.
   This allows testing the logic of the remote installer without actually doing
  remote calls. Renamed get_cache_sources to just sources. Renamed get_caches
  to source_info.  The problem is that cache is too generic and there are
  actually several things that we will cache in the system.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb: Fixed calls to get_cache_sources to
  use the new name sources.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb: Changed interface to From_installed_gems
  class method. Reordered rescue clauses so that the syntax exception might
  actually be handled.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Dumped the check_gem_subdirectories method to use
  the almost identical ensure_gem_subdirectories method. Added comments to
  ensure_gem_subdirectories. Only attempt to create the gem subdirectories if
  we can actually write them. Deleted check_gem_subdirectories.  

  * rubygems/bin/gem_server: Added date of last file modification to header of
  /yaml.  This is in preparation for using a head command with date/time
  stamping in fetching the source cache.  

