2004-08-29  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/ubygems.rb: added comment  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb:
  Added an exception: FilePermissionError which checks to ensure write access
  to the install/uninstall/rdoc destination directories and raises a nice error
  instead of the standard one.  

2004-08-28  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/ubygems.rb: file to enable ruby -rubygems...it just contains
  'require "rubygems"'  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: stubs  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: commented out stub addition and removal
   

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: loadpath  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/loadpath_manager.rb: this
  adds all the loadpath_manager stuff with the 'ultimate require hack' to
  rubygems.rb.  Also, require_gem methods body has been extracted into a method
  Gem.activate that differs in the calling signature in that the second param
  is a boolean that determines whether to autorequire or not.  

2004-08-27  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: Removed spurious (and inaccurate)
  comment.  

2004-08-27  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: ask_yes_no  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: changed all places where ask was
  used with [Yn] to ask_yes_no  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/user_interaction.rb: added method 'ask_yes_no' with
  optional optional second param (true/false) as the default.  returns true for
  yes, false for no  

2004-08-26  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/loadpath_manager.rb: optimize the searching and
  account for requiring .rb files  

2004-08-25  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/loadpath_manager.rb: the loadpath manager is used to
  automatically require a gem (with require_gem) when a require match is found
  in a file in one of the gems paths.  the loadpath manager is optimized for
  minimal impact on the performance of ruby at runtime (requires should not
  slow to too much).  a change is needed, and not yet checked in, to
  rubygems.rb to allow this to work.  

2004-08-23  Gavin Sinclair <gsinclair@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_parse_commands.rb: * lib/rubygems/installer.rb: Library
  stubs are now installed as per 'library_stubs' gemspec attribute.  A stub is
  (still) also installed for the 'autorequire' attribute.  All library stub
  handling refactored into two new classes: LibraryStubs and LibraryStub.  *
  test/test_parse_commands.rb: as per 2004-08-17 below, the 'update' command
  takes --rdoc as its default now.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: Added an entry for 2004-08-06 that was somehow
  overlooked.  

