2004-06-25  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated changelog  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb, rubygems/test/functional.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_parse_commands.rb, rubygems/test/test_process_commands.rb:
  Updated help commands.  Renamed rubygems-info to environment  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/bin/gem_server,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/command.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/gem_commands.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/user_interaction.rb, rubygems/test/functional.rb,
  rubygems/test/mockgemui.rb, rubygems/test/test_command.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_parse_commands.rb: Flexible command names, install takes
  args for gem names, better error handling  

  * rubygems/bin/gem2: Removed Gem2  

  * rubygems/test/test_version_comparison.rb: Updated pessimistic operator
  tests.  

  * rubygems/test/functional.rb: Updated functions tests to new command
  structure.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/version.rb: Changed the pessimistic operator to "~>" 
  (think approximately greater than).  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb: Added rubygems-info and version
  commands. Added error trapping in the run command. No args returns a status
  of 1 (again).  

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Promoted gem2 into the spot of honor (i.e. gem).  

  * rubygems/test/test_check_command.rb, rubygems/test/test_parse_commands.rb,
  rubygems/test/test_process_commands.rb: Use CommandManager.new for testing!  

  * rubygems/test/test_command.rb: *** empty log message ***  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/command.rb: Command is now the superclass of all
  commands (instead of the prototype).  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cmd_manager.rb: Removed UI from command manager.
  CommandManager can be created with new or instance.  Instance always
  references the same manager. Management of the common options has been moved
  to the Command class. All commands are now their own class.  

