  output.  

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/TODO,
  rubygems/examples/application/an-app.gemspec,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb:
  Add arbitrary files for rdoc to process as per Jim's request.  

2004-06-04  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/TODO, rubygems/bin/gem: Reformatted gem
  --search and --list output so that multiple versions of the same gem are
  compressed into a single entry with the version number in parens.  

2004-06-01  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/TODO: Updated TODO list.  This list probably represents what
  version 1.0 should look likea.  

2004-06-01  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog: updated ChangeLog  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/version.rb: Removed explicit >* from REQ_RE.  (OP_RE
  has it embedded). Simplified the initialization of Version::Requirement by
  moving smarts into parse (where it should be). Simplified satisfied_by? by
  using the all? method. Added an explicit one requirement satisfy? method.
  Parse now checks agains RE rather than spliting and joining integer arrays.  

  * rubygems/test/test_version_comparison.rb: Reworked the version tests to not
  depend on dynamic test method generation.  

  * rubygems/test/insure_session.rb: Added require rubygems to insure_session. 

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/version.rb: String conversion now converts to a
  single element list. Dependency attribute is now named version_requirements
  (note the "s"). Added "bump" method to handle the pessimistic comparison
  operator. Reworked requirement class to not inherit from version and to
  support multiple versions.  Now using lambda to implement operators.
  Requirements now expect an array of requirement strings.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Modified require_gem to take a list of version
  requirements.  

2004-05-31  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/ChangeLog, rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: gemspec now supports #rdoc_options,
  to which you can append strings that will be passed to rdoc as additional
  options.  

2004-05-30  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/Rakefile, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Pre-released version update  

