  defined?(@platform) to silence some -w warnings.  

2003-11-29  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem_server, rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb: updated to
  support /doc URL to generate list of installed gems w/doc link for rdoc
  generated links.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb: minor format change of error message 

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems/builder.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb:
  instantiates DocManager now. errors out on no install of RDoc. warns if
  .gemspec does not specify having rdoc, but rdoc is generated  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/doc_manager.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/format.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb:
  added capability to generate rdoc on install of gem (--gen-rdoc). this doc is
  placed in Gem.dir+doc+gem.full_name fixed but in installer when moving to
  format (not calling each) added doc manager to add/remove documenatation
  (right now only rdoc)  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: should not define the attr_readers
  for requirements/dependencies so undef is unnecessary  

2003-11-29  Jim Weirich <jim.weirich@gmail.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: Undefing dependencies and
  requirements removes warning when used with -w.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: Using defined?($GEM_PATH) avoids warning when
  used with -w switch.  

2003-11-28  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb,
