  ... will be used to autogenerate rdoc  

2003-11-28  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/validator.rb: Rdoc added  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/validator.rb: A little rearranging of the
  validation/alien code.  It's still ugly, but at least it's in its own file
  now. :)  

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Removed a little cruft.  

2003-11-27  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Print success message for each gem *not* containing
  errors.  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: Preliminary support
  for gem directory validation (--alien).  Looks for bad or missing gem files,
  missing spec files, files installed that aren't part of the gem, checksum
  mismatches, etc.  Very ugly code.  Very ugly output.  Work in progress.  

2003-11-24  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: change full_name to include
  platform  

2003-11-24  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Option for HTTP Proxy server for remote-install.  Not yet
  implemented.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/builder.rb: Removed a stray \" in builder's success
  message  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: Leaving escape in but commenting
  out its functionality because it hosed some other things up.  Need to revisit
  this for the case where:  s.summary = "Chad's Thing" # It's the apostrophe  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: Escape quotes to avoid invalid
  gemspecs in the #{Gem.dir}/specifications directory  

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Less ugly error message on file IO problems.  

2003-11-23  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Very simple support for validating a gem.  Will probably
  move this into the libs eventually.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/builder.rb: Generate MD5 checksum for gem and store
  it in the file.  Will be used to validate gem file before installation.  

2003-11-22  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/install.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb:
  remote-install sources are now installed as a ruby gem at the time of
  rubygems installation.  sources gemspec included in the rubygems
  distribution.  

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Allow gem info by --version  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb: Fixed the bug I
  introduced by fixing Rich's bug with gem cache caching. ;)  Gem::Cache now
  has a #refresh! method.  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: - Fixed bug in Gem.cache (though
  we may want to revisit it for in-memory caching - Command line configurable
  version for uninstall  

2003-11-22  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb: rdoc'd search method  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/version.rb, rubygems/test/test_version_comparison.rb:
  removed search_by_name because search does the same thing. 
  version::requirement was updated to that if you did not specific a version
  operation, it assumes an = sign.  updated tests accordingly  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: allow
  version to be specified in uninstall (if called programatically)  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: >
  moved all searching into cache..and now search by name/version and return an
  ordered list (.last == highest version). > modified uninstaller to allow
  selecting a specific version to uninstall if multiple versions are installed.
  > implemented comparison function on specification. > changed require_gem to
  use new search of cache function  

2003-11-22  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added ability
  to specify optional version requirement for remote installations  

  * rubygems/test/test_remote_installer.rb: Removed carriage returns  

  * rubygems/bin/gem_server: Converted from getopts to optparse.  

2003-11-21  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: changed the order in which operations are
  performed in require_gem. it now requires dependent gems prior to adding the
  require_paths to a gem. otherwise we could have had a LoadError on a
  dependent gem but the paths were already added...potential problem  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: updated to ensure
  (specifications/cache) directories exist for a provided path  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: updated rdoc  

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems/builder.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb:
  fixed various bugs with the $GEM_PATH stuff, specifically on uninstall. 
  Also, changed to allow specifying a directory on install (--dir) and force
  install (--force).  Changed the builder generated ruby header to use
  optparse.  

2003-11-21  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Remote installation of
  dependencies now works.  It downloads all dependent gems or errors out. 
  Fixed bug in require_gem.  Wrong call to cache.  

2003-11-21  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem, rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb:
  added capability to support multiple paths $GEM_PATH in Ruby and RUBY_GEMS in
  the ARGV.  Lots of changes were needed to support this.  also added the
  --force and --dir options to gem installtion  

2003-11-21  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem: Switched to optparse. Not a whole lot gained, but it
  seems to be the way Ruby is going.  It's nice not to have to do the "when"
  stuff, I guess.  

2003-11-20  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/remote_installer.rb: Added chadfowler.com to the
  hardcoded remote install list.  Fixed a dangling YAML.load that broke
  uninstall.  

2003-11-20  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb: fixed bug in loading rubygems  

2003-11-20  Chad Fowler <chad@chadfowler.com>

  * rubygems/bin/gem_server, rubygems/bin/gem_server.cgi: require 'yaml' :)  

2003-11-20  Richard Kilmer <rich@infoether.com>

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems.rb, rubygems/lib/rubygems/cache.rb,
  rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: changed the format of stuff stored in
  the spec directory to ruby instead of YAML.  This allows us to not have to
  load yaml in 'require_gem'.  switched the specification list to a Cache
  object.  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/installer.rb: write the spec file in ruby and not in
  yaml format (in the spec dir)  

  * rubygems/lib/rubygems/specification.rb: added to_ruby method to generate a
  ruby string that can be eval'ed in to build a Gem Specification  

